choices.text:
walking from the main house. You can ask Wildor or Carolyn to drive you if you need.

You will share this house with your hosts and if you want, with other guests.

The bedroom is spacious despite the adorable window at the top of the bed. This window is a real great sleeping amenity. There is a fan by the bed and Linda and Garrett have asked us to close the windows if you use the fan, because they were afraid that we would consume a lot of electricity (well, not much in Panama!).

The air conditioning is installed in the room but isn’t used… mostly because it is rare that it’s necessary. Carolyn installed a couple fans also in the suite.

Linda and Garrett have a lot of rooms so you can have plenty of privacy for both parties, with the kitchen (fridge, oven, microwave, coffee maker, hood, etc.). Just outside the kitchen there is a terrace table for meals.

Your hosts are always available and ready to help you.

The entrance/ exit is very easy whether you drive or not because there is a mailbox in the building opposite where you enter and you have a private parking lot to the left of the suite.

Outdoors, on our side of the house, you will find the famous national flowers of Panama and you will have a private living room area, with bar/ cocktail and a shaded little pool (well, not so little actually).

Rates: the exchange rate was around 1 for approximatively 1.
